00:02:54.650 --> 00:02:56.290
Know your metrics.

00:02:56.290 --> 00:02:58.680
All right, what is LTV
and why does it matter?

00:02:58.680 --> 00:03:01.320
LTV simply stands
for Life Time Value.

00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:03.259
If you didn't know
that, now you do.

00:03:03.259 --> 00:03:05.550
It's one of the key metrics
that everyone looks at when

00:03:05.550 --> 00:03:06.900
it comes to game development.

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:09.390
It's something that you
buy against when you're

00:03:09.390 --> 00:03:11.040
doing your user
acquisition campaigns,

00:03:11.040 --> 00:03:13.410
and it's obviously what
you look to when you're

00:03:13.410 --> 00:03:14.820
trying to monetize your games.

00:03:14.820 --> 00:03:17.670
This is the absolute value
of the average custom

00:03:17.670 --> 00:03:19.110
in your game.

00:03:19.110 --> 00:03:21.240
Now, it's a bit
different in games

00:03:21.240 --> 00:03:23.820
as a service, which you often
see in mobile, versus what

00:03:23.820 --> 00:03:26.529
you would ordinarily see
in a packaged business

00:03:26.529 --> 00:03:28.820
that you would see, say, in
GameStop or somewhere else.

00:03:28.820 --> 00:03:31.470
In a packaged games business,
you've got a binary outcome.

00:03:31.470 --> 00:03:35.160
You either have $0 or you have
$60 from your customer-- one

00:03:35.160 --> 00:03:37.020
or the other,
nothing in between.

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:39.790
With games as a service,
it's a bit different.

00:03:39.790 --> 00:03:41.370
There's no barrier to entry.

00:03:41.370 --> 00:03:42.030
People come in.

00:03:42.030 --> 00:03:44.585
It's free to download.

00:03:44.585 --> 00:03:45.960
And then you have
this experience

00:03:45.960 --> 00:03:48.450
where you're providing
a service as the player

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:49.720
goes through your game.

00:03:49.720 --> 00:03:52.620
So LTV is not a function
of a single price point.

00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:55.869
LTV is a function of
engagement times the value

00:03:55.869 --> 00:03:57.660
that you offer your
customers and the value

00:03:57.660 --> 00:04:00.040
that they give you back
in terms of dollars.

00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:02.980
So LTV in this case,
for games as a service,

00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:05.700
is engagement times value.

00:04:05.700 --> 00:04:09.360
So, Fred's going to come up in
