00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:10.950
He's got some
amazing slides on it.

00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:13.033
I'm going to talk about
engagement really quickly,

00:04:13.033 --> 00:04:15.418
just to talk about how do
developers drive engagement,

00:04:15.418 --> 00:04:16.709
think about it, and measure it.

00:04:16.709 --> 00:04:19.430
So let's think about
measuring it first.

00:04:19.430 --> 00:04:21.360
There's a few ways to
measure engagement.

00:04:21.360 --> 00:04:23.670
There is the traditional
ways of session length

00:04:23.670 --> 00:04:26.430
and sessions per day, and
that stickiness factor

00:04:26.430 --> 00:04:28.800
that you often hear
about-- daily active users

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:30.025
over monthly active users.

00:04:30.025 --> 00:04:32.910
Hint-- that should
be at least 15%.

00:04:32.910 --> 00:04:34.780
But hard retention,
hard retention

00:04:34.780 --> 00:04:38.760
is one that we look at all the
time-- D1, D7, D30-- absolutely

00:04:38.760 --> 00:04:39.600
critical.

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:42.635
And it's critical for a
very, very obvious reason,

00:04:42.635 --> 00:04:44.010
but I'm going to
tell you it just

00:04:44.010 --> 00:04:47.190
to make sure it sticks
and you never forget it.

00:04:47.190 --> 00:04:49.177
You can't make money
from your users.

00:04:49.177 --> 00:04:51.510
You can't offer them value
and they can't give you value

00:04:51.510 --> 00:04:53.670
back in terms of their
dollars if they're not

00:04:53.670 --> 00:04:54.940
playing the game.

00:04:54.940 --> 00:04:58.620
So if your D7 and D30s are
low, if players are not

00:04:58.620 --> 00:05:00.840
sticking around in your
game, simply-- again,

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:01.770
very obviously,
you're not going to be

00:05:01.770 --> 00:05:02.970
able to make money from them.

00:05:02.970 --> 00:05:04.950
This is why it's absolutely
one of the most critical things

00:05:04.950 --> 00:05:05.760
out there.

00:05:05.760 --> 00:05:10.990
It's the number one predictor
of success in LTV is retention.

